==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Oust
<hw>Oust</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Ousted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Ousting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>oster</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦ocir⟧ter</ets>, prob. fr. L. <ets>obstare</ets> to oppose, hence,
to forbid, take away. See <er>Obstacle</er>, and cf.
<er>Ouster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take away; to
remove.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Multiplication of actions upon the case were rare, formerly, and
thereby wager of law <qex>ousted</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M.
Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To eject; to expel; to turn out.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From mine own earldom foully <qex>ousted</qex> me.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ouster</ent>⟦br⟧
